"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-paris-2024-olympics-the-only-schedule-you-need-for-the-rest-of-the-games\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbParis 2024 Olympics: The only schedule you need for the rest of the games  The Olympics have been an absolute joy, so do not miss the biggest events between now and Sunday.  The Paris 2024 Olympics have served up so much drama but there is plenty more to come in France. Besides, Team SA still has medals to contest.  View the full schedule via the Paris 2024official website.  Tatjana Smith became the most decorated Olympian in South African history with her haul oftwo medalsin Paris. She claimed gold in the 100m breaststroke and silver in the 200m event, an exact reversal of her antics in Tokyo. The other Team SA medallists in 2024 areAlan Hatherlywho\\u00a0won bronze in the men's Mountain Bike (MTB) cross-country race; South Africa's first Olympic cycling medal since 1956, some 68 years ago, and theRugby Sevens sidewho claimed bronze by beating Australia.  30-year-old sprinter Akani Simbine, a picture of consistency for the better part of a decade, heartbreakingly missed out on a medal in one of the most iconic 100m finals in Olympic history. Last-placed Jamaican Oblique Seville crossed the line in 9.91, which would have claimed fourth in Tokyo three years ago, just to illustrate how competitive this race was. It's a familiar feeling for Simbine with consecutive fourth-placed finishes in Olympic finals and a fifth-placed finish in Rio in 2016. He can hold his head extremely high.  For those interested in the GOAT debate in tennis,Novak Djokovic finally drew a line under all thatwith a gold medal to complete his set of tennis accolades.  Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.com. Meanwhile, you can also send a WhatsApp to 060 011 021 1. Follow@TheSAnews on XandThe South African on Facebookfor your social fix.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"